-- French Energy Minister Vows to Shut Nuclear Plant: JDD
-- B y   M a r k   D e e n
-- 2013-07-22T07:41:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-22/french-energy-minister-vows-to-shut-nuclear-plant-jdd-correct-.html
(Corrects reference to Proglio in second paragraph in story
published yesterday.)  Philippe Martin, who became France’s
energy and environment minister July 4, said the government will
close the Fessenheim nuclear power plant by the end of 2016,
according to an interview published in Le Journal du Dimanche
*Martin also said that Henri Proglio’s role as chief executive
of Elecricite de France SA doesn’t “pose a problem” for the
government, according to the interview  To contact the reporter on this story:
